+# ZenovFS1 mount hardening for 0.1.1
+
+## Threat
+
+The persistent ATA volume is attacker-controlled at the storage boundary. A corrupted superblock or entry table must not be able to influence kernel memory before its geometry and bounded metadata are validated.
+
+The previous mount path trusted `entry_sectors`, `data_start` and `slot_sectors` after checking only the magic, version and entry count. In particular, `load_entries()` copied `entry_sectors × 512` bytes into a fixed 8,192-byte entry array. A forged value above 16 therefore created a direct kernel-memory overwrite before policy initialization.
+
+## Enforced geometry
+
+The shared validator now requires:
+
+- exact `ZENOVFS1` magic and schema 1;
+- a non-zero device-bounded LBA28 sector count;
+- `1..128` entries;
+- an entry-table sector count exactly matching `entry_count × 64` bytes;
+- a data region beginning after all metadata;
+- a slot size of `1..128` sectors, keeping a file within the 64 KiB kernel/user buffers;
+- enough non-overflowing data sectors for every slot;
+- non-zero generation, a bounded printable label and zeroed reserved bytes.
+
+## Entry-table validation
+
+Before any path lookup or recovery mutation, every entry is checked for:
+
+- fully zero unused slots;
+- known type and flag values;
+- a terminated canonical absolute path with no control characters, empty components, `.` or `..`;
+- bounded file sizes and zero-only directory metadata;
+- valid transaction/committed recovery references;
+- no unrelated duplicate paths or shared recovery references;
+- an existing directory parent.
+
+The same checks run again after interrupted-write recovery. Recovery is allowed to remove an old entry only when its type, flags and exact path match the committed replacement.
+
+Runtime path normalization also rejects control characters, preventing path-based serial/audit line injection.
+
+## Evidence
+
+`tests/zenovfs_mount_validation_test.cpp` includes the exact production validator and exercises malformed geometry, unterminated and control-character paths, oversized files, invalid directory metadata, missing parents, duplicate paths and forged recovery references under ASan and UBSan.
+
+The existing strict kernel build, deterministic image generation, COW fault matrix and QEMU workflows continue to run on the same commit.
+
+## Boundary
+
+This validation prevents malformed metadata from causing memory corruption or unsafe recovery. ZenovFS1 still uses FNV-1a only as an accidental-corruption checksum. An offline attacker able to rewrite both data and metadata can recompute it. Authenticated block storage, fs-verity-style Merkle trees, encryption and a hardware-backed rollback boundary remain unimplemented.
